    public class FullConceptDescriptor
extends ConceptGround
implements ConceptExpression.Definition, ConceptExpression.Disjoint<FullConceptDescriptor>, ConceptExpression.Equivalent<FullConceptDescriptor>, ConceptExpression.Sub<FullConceptDescriptor>, ConceptExpression.Super<FullConceptDescriptor>, ConceptExpression.Instance<LinkIndividualDesc>
    This is an example of a 'compound' Concept Descriptor as it implements more than one ClassExpression (aka ConceptExpression). Axioms in this descriptor's internal state (i.e., OWLOOP representation) can be synchronized to/from an OWL ontology. FullConceptDescriptor can synchronize all the axioms, that are based on the following ClassExpressions:
    • ConceptExpression.Equivalent: to describe that a Class is equivalent to another Class.
    • ConceptExpression.Disjoint: to describe that a Class is disjoint to another Class.
    • ConceptExpression.Sub: to describe that a Class subsumes another Class.
    • ConceptExpression.Super: to describe that a Class is a super-class of another Class.
    • ConceptExpression.Instance: to describe an Individual of a Class.
    • ConceptExpression.Definition: to describe the definition of a Class..
